    <text>
        <body>

            <pb n="1"/>

            <p rend="align(right)"><placeName>New York</placeName>&#44; Monday of the Portion of Exodus
                    <date>5612</date><lb/> &#40;c. December&#41;</p>
            <p>May God shower life and blessings upon the head of my friend<lb/> the honored and
                praised&#44; perfect in knowledge of the Torah&#44;<lb/> the spiritual&#44;
                    <addressee>Yithak Isaac of the family Leeser</addressee><lb/>
                <del>the</del> Friend of my soul&#44;<lb/>
            </p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">Many days have passed and gone during which I<lb/> have not heard
                from you&#44; nor received any reply to letters<lb/> written to you. And I did not
                know the cause why and<lb/> wherefore you refrained from raising the pen to tells
                    <add>&#63;</add><lb/> about the what and how of things. I fear lest there
                gave<lb/> up a misunderstanding between us&#44; and the cord of
                lo<add>&#63;</add><lb/> be broken which has <del>been</del> tied us since I set foot
                in <add>&#63;</add><lb/> town and to this day. First I wrote to you that I<lb/> paid
                the money for the prayer&#8211;books which I took<lb/> from my friend
                    <persName>Goldsmith</persName>. Immediately upon recei<add>pt</add><lb/> of the
                money I shall send you also the rest. I do n<add>ot</add><lb/> know whether I am to
                give the money to <persName>Goldsmith</persName><lb/> to <hi rend="underline"
                    >&#63;</hi>. I also wrote that I received a total of<lb/> &#36;1.50 from Gross
                &#38; Co. for you. To whom shall I <add>&#63;</add><lb/> I&#44; therefore&#63;
                hope&#63; that you&#63; my dear friend&#63; will<lb/> not be lazily silent. I also
                want to let you know<lb/> that a meeting <del>will take</del> took place in my
                    congregat<add>ion</add><lb/> about establishing a Talmud Torah. My friend<lb/>
                the learned Rabbi <persName>Moses Raphael</persName> addressed</p>

            <pb n="2"/>
            <p>the meeting. I too read a few words&#44; which&#44; if y<add>ou</add><lb/> so
                wish&#44; I shall send to you that you might offer<lb/> them up upon the altar of
                the leaves &#40;pages&#41;.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">I have nothing more to write&#44; except my/ blessing.....</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">From <del>his</del> your friend and ever&#8211;ready<lb/> servant<lb/>
                <persName role="author">Simon Cohen Naht</persName> or<lb/>
                <persName role="author">Noht</persName><lb/> 133 Mulberry St. </p>
            <p>Please <del>bring</del> include the enclosed composition in your
                Occide<add>nt</add><lb/> and print it for three months<lb/> &#40;was it an
                advertisement&#63;&#41;</p>


        </body>
